# install tweepy in windows
# 1. download tweepy packages from github: https://github.com/tweepy/tweepy
# 2. unzip the package on desktop
# 3. rename the folder to tweepy
# 4. change path in windows settings: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/7054424/python-not-recognised-as-a-command 
# 5. in windows cmd window, cd desktop\tweepy
# 6. python setup.py install

# install twython in windows
# 1. download twyton packages from github: https://github.com/ryanmcgrath/twython
# 2. unzip the package on desktop
# 3. rename the folder to twython
# 4. in windows cmd window, cd desktop\twython
# 5. python setup.py install
